    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Samanea inopinata are quercetin, a potent antioxidant and anti-inflammatory flavonoid that has been shown to inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Kaempferol, another flavonoid present in Samanea inopinata, possesses anti-inflammatory, anti-oxidative, and anti-cancer properties due to its ability to scavenge free radicals and inhibit the activity of pro-inflammatory enzymes. Gallic acid, a polyphenolic compound found in Samanea inopinata, has been demonstrated to exhibit anti-inflammatory, anti-oxidative, and antimicrobial activities, as well as the ability to inhibit the growth of cancer cells. Ellagic acid, another polyphenolic constituent of Samanea inopinata, has been found to possess anti-cancer properties, as it can inhibit the growth of cancer cells by inducing apoptosis and inhibiting the activity of certain enzymes involved in cancer progression. The flavonoids present in Samanea inopinata, including quercetin and kaempferol, contribute to its overall antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activity, making it a potential therapeutic agent for the treatment of various diseases.",
