    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Samanea inopinata improperly include experiencing nausea and vomiting due to the presence of toxic compounds such as samaneanin and isoflavones, which can cause gastrointestinal irritation. Allergic reactions may also occur due to the plant's sap, leading to symptoms like hives, itching, and difficulty breathing. Cardiac arrest can be triggered in individuals with pre-existing heart conditions due to the toxic compounds' effect on the cardiovascular system. Furthermore, excessive consumption of Samanea inopinata may lead to tachycardia, an abnormally fast heart rate, which can be life-threatening in severe cases. It is essential to note that improper use of Samanea inopinata can exacerbate these side effects, emphasizing the need for caution and proper handling.",
    "uses": "Samanea inopinata is a species of plant that has been used in traditional medicine for various purposes. It is said to have anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties, which may help treat wounds and infections. The plant's leaves and bark are often used to make teas and infusions that are believed to aid in digestion and reduce fever. Some studies suggest that Samanea inopinata may also have antioxidant and cytotoxic effects, although more research is needed to confirm its efficacy. Further investigation is necessary to fully understand the medicinal potential of this plant.",
    "taxonomy": "Samanea inopinata is classified as a species of flowering plant in the family Fabaceae. It is a legume native to the tropical regions of Central and South America. This plant is part of the genus Samanea, which includes several other species of trees and shrubs. Samanea inopinata is a relatively rare and lesser-known species within the genus. Further research is needed to fully understand its classification and relationships within the plant kingdom.",
    "benefits": "Samanea inopinata is believed to have various health benefits due to its rich nutritional content and medicinal properties. The leaves and seeds of the plant are said to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties, which can help in reducing the risk of chronic diseases such as heart disease and cancer. Additionally, the plant is used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments, including fever, cough, and respiratory problems. The antioxidant properties of Samanea inopinata may also help in protecting against oxidative stress and cell damage. Further research is needed to fully understand the potential health benefits of this plant.",
    "parts": "Samanea inopinata is a plant species native to tropical forests, and research suggests that its medicinal parts may include the bark, leaves, and roots. The plant has been traditionally used in various folk remedies, although its efficacy and safety have not been extensively scientifically proven. The bark of Samanea inopinata is believed to possess anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. Studies are needed to fully understand the medicinal properties of the plant and its potential applications. Further research is required to isolate and characterize the bioactive compounds in Samanea inopinata.",
    "intro": "Samanea inopinata, also known as the \"African samanea,\" is a plant species native to tropical Africa, belonging to the Fabaceae family of legumes. It is traditionally used in folk medicine for its potential health benefits, including anti-inflammatory, antimicrobial, and antiparasitic properties, which may help alleviate symptoms of fever, cough, and respiratory issues. The bioactive constituents of Samanea inopinata include flavonoids, phenolic acids, and saponins, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional herbal medicine, Samanea inopinata is often prepared into teas, infusions, or decoctions, which are used to treat various ailments, and it may also be made into capsules or tinctures for convenience."
